 Shakespeare.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Apr 2022) 0aCultural appropriation. 0aLatin AmericansxCultural assimilation. 4aLiterary Studies. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / Drama.2bisacsh1 aAlvarez, Frankie J., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBoffone, Trevor, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBurbano, Diana, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCruz, Migdalia, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDeCure, Cynthia Santos, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDella Gatta, Carla, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 aEscalante, Alejandra, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aEspinosa, Micha, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFalocco, Joe, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFerrell, Catherine Socarras, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGatta, Carla Della, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGillen, Katherine, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGodinez, Henry, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGonzález, José Cruz, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGreenberg, Marissa, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLopez-Rios, Michelle, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLozano, David, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMolina, Daniel José, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aRuiz, Jerry, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSaltveit, Olga Sanche